# =============================================================================
# .trivyignore — Suppress known unfixable CVEs for Trivy scanning
#
# Add CVE IDs here ONLY when:
#   1. The vulnerability has no available fix in Alpine upstream
#   2. The risk has been assessed and accepted
#   3. A comment explains WHY the CVE is suppressed
#
# Format: One CVE ID per line, with explanatory comment above
# Example:
#   # nginx:alpine - buffer overflow in libxml2, no fix available as of 2026-02
#   CVE-2024-XXXXX
#
# Review this file regularly and remove entries when fixes become available.
# Trivy CI uses: --ignore-unfixed --severity CRITICAL,HIGH --trivyignores .trivyignore
# =============================================================================

# nginx:alpine-slim — OpenSSL heap use-after-free in PKCS7_verify() (HIGH).
# Fix openssl 3.5.7-r0 is not yet in the Alpine 3.23 branch; the Dockerfile's
# `apk upgrade` already pulls the latest available (3.5.6-r0) and will pick up
# 3.5.7-r0 automatically once backported. Low risk: the image serves static
# assets via nginx and does not exercise PKCS7_verify. Assessed 2026-06-11.
# Remove when 3.5.7-r0 lands in Alpine 3.23. Review by 2026-07-11.
CVE-2026-45447
